Key Match Events: Niclas Füllkrug headed in an 85th minute goal to give Germany a 2-1 comeback victory over Netherlands.
Joey Veerman volleyed in following a mistake by defender Maximilian Mittelstädt in the 4th minute.
Maximilian Mittelstädt made amends with a perfectly curled shot into the top corner to level the score.
Post-Match Reflections: Coach Julian Nagelsmann expressed that the win does a lot of good for the team and praised their spirit and mix.
Nagelsmann noted that the team adapted their game in terms of positions and dominated the last 15 minutes.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Germany had more than 70% possession in the first half hour.
Jamal Musiala forced a fine save from Dutch keeper Bart Verbruggen in the 76th minute.
Bart Verbruggen stopped Thomas Müller's effort to keep Netherlands in the game.
Others: The match was held at Deutsche Bank Park in Frankfurt, Germany with an attendance of 48,390.
Germany will next play Ukraine in Nuremberg on June 3 before taking on Greece in Moenchengladbach on June 7.
